From: PS3 Custom Toolchain
Subject: [PATCH] cell64lv2: define __ILP32__ when default ILP32 mode is in effect

When -mlp64 is NOT in effect (the default ILP32 hybrid mode), GCC's
TARGET_OS_CPP_BUILTINS macro emitted neither __LP64__ nor __ILP32__.
Portable C/C++ headers that branch on these macros (third-party
configure probes, libc++ feature tests, GMP / MPFR / OpenSSL header
guards) saw no data-model macro at all and either fell through to a
wrong default or failed configure-time detection.

Default ILP32 hybrid is genuinely ILP32: sizeof(int) == sizeof(long) ==
sizeof(void *) == 4.  __ILP32__ + _ILP32 are the canonical macros to
emit for that data model.  This patch adds the else branch.

The matching positive case (TARGET_LP64) was already emitting __LP64__
and _LP64; this patch fills in the symmetric ILP32 case.

--- a/gcc/config/rs6000/cell64lv2.h
+++ b/gcc/config/rs6000/cell64lv2.h
@@ -249,11 +249,17 @@
       builtin_assert ("cpu=powerpc64");		\
       builtin_assert ("machine=powerpc64");		\
 						\
-      /* Data-model axis: only when -mlp64 is in effect. */ \
+      /* Data-model axis: TARGET_LP64 is the multilib opt-in; \
+         default is ILP32 hybrid. */ \
       if (TARGET_LP64)				\
 	{					\
 	  builtin_define ("__LP64__");		\
 	  builtin_define ("_LP64");			\
 	}					\
+      else						\
+	{					\
+	  builtin_define ("__ILP32__");		\
+	  builtin_define ("_ILP32");			\
+	}					\
     }							\
   while (0)

